  "mitigation_currently_implemented": "Engage upstream DDoS mitigation/scrubbing or request upstream traffic shaping (have the ISP or edge provider rate-limit or scrub volumetric ICMP at the network edge so abusive traffic is dropped before it consumes local capacity).",
  "comments": "I added a second Snort IPS inline (snort-ids-2) and placed it between the Internet and the FortiGate, providing additional inline detection/blocking at the WAN edge to supplement the first Snort device. While true upstream ISP scrubbing can't be performed inside this digital twin environment, adding another inline Snort simulates strengthened edge filtering and increases the likelihood that outbound ICMP floods will be detected and dropped before reaching the Internet. This complements earlier mitigations (host nftables, iptables, kernel nftables XDP-style rules, FortiGate DoS policy, switch storm-control and port-security). Validation: re-run the hping3 attack and observe packet drops on the Internet link, Snort alerts (if accessible), and decreased FortiGate DoS triggers.\n\nNote: Snort devices are pre-configured and shouldn't be modified; I only added and linked them inline per the instructions.",
  "device_identifier": "snort-ids-2",
  "commands": [
    "add_network_device snort snort-ids-2",
    "link_network_devices snort-ids-2 fortigate-firewall",
    "link_network_devices Internet snort-ids-2"
  ]
}
